This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-fontTools layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

Dependencies
============

This layer depends on the following layers:

  - `meta`
  - `meta-python`

Ensure that these layers are included in your build environment before adding `meta-fontTools`.

Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the meta-fontTools layer to the GitHub repository issues or pull requests.

Maintainer: Chetan Dandolu <chetan@novelmicrodevices.com>

Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-fontTools layer to your build
 II. Python3-fonttools recipe
III. Misc

I. Adding the meta-fontTools layer to your build
================================================

To include the meta-fontTools layer in your build, add it to your `bblayers.conf` file:

```bash
bitbake-layers add-layer meta-fontTools
```

II. Python3-fonttools recipe
=============================

This layer currently includes the following recipe:

- **python3-fonttools_4.53.0.bb**: This recipe builds and installs the FontTools library, which is a set of tools to manipulate font files. It is useful to load backend_pdf module for matplotlib.

III. Misc
=========

This layer is in the early stages of development. Future updates may include additional recipes or enhancements. Contributions and patches are welcome.

